This is a very important thing to keep in mind and should be done all the time with out being reminded.<br>
In most raids we are dealing with loads of critters that can and will kill us all given the chance.  Otherwise it would not really be a raid.<br>
All raids work with the idea of a puller, MT and so on.<br>
The idea of a "base" is to insure that no one is too close to the puller and tagger, so that if something goes wrong, agro does not pass to the main body of the raid.<br>
The Raid Leader will set up the base in places best suited to avoiding unnecessary agro.  If you go past the base you will most likely get agro and possibly kill the whole raid.<br>
So here are some general rules for all raids:<br>
Never pass the Main Tank.<br>
Always form a Base or camp in the area the Raid Leader is at and never pass them or the MT.<br>
Do not wander around.<br>
Do not rush up to engage anything, always wait for the MT to do so.<br>
<br>
If you always follow these basic guidelines, we will be able to avoid agro and control our kills.  This is the only way we can win in many cases.<br>
Remember, if in doubt about anything, ask.<br>
